AI is by definition a copy/imitation, because no matter how good or unlike its source material it is, it is an algorithmically created thing based on other work, so it cannot be an original creation. By that same token, and 'original creation' from a human is obviously based on their preferred styles, pieces, and influences generally, and depending how contrived you perceive it to be, it is arguably not an 'original creation'. Again, I don't feel the validity of AI can be found in how well it can deceive people into thinking it is original, because even human made art is contrived to some extent. It is the knowledge that human effort went into a piece of art that gives it merit, even if it is not a good piece of art. Art is expression, and an algorithm is not expressing anything, it is calculating it.
